last_episode_to_air.name: Hang Men
last_episode_to_air.overview: At a second trial, the prosecution aims to prove that Erik and Lyle are cold-blooded killers. After the verdict, the brothers face a new reality.

name: Monsters
overview: The story of the Menéndez brothers, who were convicted in 1996 of murdering their parents José and Mary Louise “Kitty” Menéndez.

seasons.name: The Lyle and Erik Menendez Story

episodes.name: Blame It on the Rain
episodes.overview: Plagued by dark thoughts after the murders, Erik opens up to his therapist and shares disturbing details that put the doctor in a difficult position.

episodes.name: Spree
episodes.overview: After throwing suspicion elsewhere during police questioning, Lyle and Erik go on a wild spending spree while waiting for Jose's will to be read.

episodes.name: Brother, Can You Spare a Dime?
episodes.overview: The brothers navigate life behind bars after police receive a tip-off about the tapes. A new defense attorney prompts Erik to talk about the past.

episodes.name: Kill or Be Killed
episodes.overview: Lyle shares painful memories of trying to live up to his father's expectations, detailing the timeline and impact of Jose's abuse and its effect on Erik.

episodes.name: The Hurt Man
episodes.overview: During an emotional conversation with Leslie, Erik gives a harrowing account of the sexual abuse and torture he experienced throughout his childhood.

episodes.name: Don't Dream It's Over
episodes.overview: The trajectory of Jose and Kitty's relationship — from their courtship through their fracturing marriage — plays out against family therapy sessions.

episodes.name: Showtime
episodes.overview: Lyle and Erik struggle to shape their defense before the trial. Then Menendez mania hits — from cheering crowds to fan mail and courtroom TV cameras.

episodes.name: Seismic Shifts
episodes.overview: A captivating witness alters courtroom dynamics, and Erik's testimony causes a sibling rift. The Menendez pop-culture moment begins to fade.

episodes.name: Hang Men
episodes.overview: At a second trial, the prosecution aims to prove that Erik and Lyle are cold-blooded killers. After the verdict, the brothers face a new reality.
